[`static func ... (Self) -> PartialRangeThrough<Self>`](/documentation/swift/closedrange/index/)Returns a partial range up to, and including, its upper bound.[`static func ... (Self) -> PartialRangeFrom<Self>`](/documentation/swift/closedrange/index/)Returns a partial range extending upward from a lower bound.[`static func ... (Self, Self) -> ClosedRange<Self>`](/documentation/swift/closedrange/index/)Returns a closed range that contains both of its bounds.[`static func ..< (Self) -> PartialRangeUpTo<Self>`](/documentation/swift/closedrange/index/)Returns a partial range up to, but not including, its upper bound.[`static func ..< (Self, Self) -> Range<Self>`](/documentation/swift/closedrange/index/)Returns a half-open range that contains its lower bound but not its upper bound.[`static func < (ClosedRange<Bound>.Index, ClosedRange<Bound>.Index) -> Bool`](/documentation/swift/closedrange/index/_(_:_:))Returns a Boolean value indicating whether the value of the first argument is less than that of the second argument.[`static func > (Self, Self) -> Bool`](/documentation/swift/closedrange/index/_(_:_:)-1fc79)Returns a Boolean value indicating whether the value of the first argument is greater than that of the second argument.[`static func >= (Self, Self) -> Bool`](/documentation/swift/closedrange/index/_=(_:_:)-52920)Returns a Boolean value indicating whether the value of the first argument is greater than or equal to that of the second argument.[`static func <= (Self, Self) -> Bool`](/documentation/swift/closedrange/index/_=(_:_:)-divd)Returns a Boolean value indicating whether the value of the first argument is less than or equal to that of the second argument.
